                              About the Library

   Primary Clients
   Locations and Hours
   Directions
   Staff

   Mission
   The Parklawn Health Library (PHL), the National Center for Health
   Statistics (NCHS) Staff Research Library (SRL) and the Agency for
   Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ) Information Resources Center
   (IRC) plan, develop and administer a national research collection and
   innovative information programs in direct support of the Department of
   Health and Human Services (HHS).

   Scope
   The combined scope of the PHL System includes: delivery of health care,
   health administration, health policy, health promotion/disease
   prevention, health services research, medical and allied sciences,
   medical sociology, public health, and the social sciences.  In
   addition, the MAIN LIBRARY has holdings in computer technology,
   international health, management sciences, mental health, and substance
   abuse.  The NCHS SRL regularly collects material on epidemiology,
   statistics, and survey research methodology.  The AHRQ IRC develops its
   collection with particular emphasis on clinical guidelines, outcomes
   research, health economics, health services research, evidence-based
   practice, and health care delivery services.

